  <bioghist id="aspace_dc89361b6ca9f1b279e1d12aec54506a">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>W. Franklin Moore was president of the Freeville public schools in the early 1920s.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_77cbeeb2360bc1f01dc85c90b472115b">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Graduation programs, alumni reunion program, alumni directory (1917) for Dryden High School; items concerning Dryden Union School and Academy, including a program for eighth grade graduation (1896) and a broadside advertising a "historical allegory and tableaux" to be presented by students (November 1892); and annual informational catalogs on Dryden Union School, 1884-1886 and 1889-1890. Also, leaflet listing teachers and students in the Freeville Public Schools, 1922, and letterhead for the 1921-1922 school year, listing the Freeville school board and teachers.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_e01e935dd9dbb0569fa08d99e3e6acf1">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>W. Franklin Moore, Collector. Dryden and Freeville Schools Collection, #1932. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
